    "chemicalDescription": [
      "Tripeptide-46 Hexapeptide-40 Decapeptide-27 Methionyl Oligopeptide-91 Dipeptide-19 sh-Polypeptide-85 Dipeptide-34 Oligopeptide-91 is a single chain recombinant fusion peptide produced by fermentation in  E. coli.  The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the gene from sh-Polypeptide-85, Tripeptide-46, Hexapeptide-40, Decapeptide-27, Oligopeptide-91, Dipeptide-19, and {29889; Dipeptide-34} with the initiation code for methionine. The fusion peptide contains 273 amino acids and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
